The paper discusses the application of Continuous Experimentation (CE) in the development and roll-out of functionalities required for self-driving vehicles. This involves complex software systems in the Web-application domain, which falls under the scope of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper also mentions safety concerns and organizational structures as major challenges, which are relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and cybernetics (cs.CY).
